\sum_{d|n}\sigma(d)\phi(\frac{n}{d})=n\tau(n),
\sum_{d|n}\tau(d)\phi(\frac{n}{d})=\sigma(n).
\sigma*\phi=(\text{id}*1)*\phi=\text{id}*1*\mu*\text{id}=\text{id}*\text{id}=\text{id}\tau
\tau*\phi=(1*1)*\phi=1*1*\mu*\text{id}=1*\text{id}=\sigma
